prompt: Write a program that uses nested for loops to print a 5x5 square pattern of asterisks (*).
answer:
Here is the code that meets the specifications:
```
for i in range(5):
    for j in range(5):
        print("*", end="")
    print()
```
This code will print a 5x5 square pattern of asterisks (*) to the console, as described in the specification. Let me know if you have any questions or if you'd like me to explain any part of the code!
